Logarithmic ValueType Demo
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph><Run FontWeight="Bold">Logarithmic ValueType Demo</Run></Paragraph><Paragraph>A chart can automatically compute an appropriate logarithmic range based on the set ValueType. A logarithmic range can also be explicitly specified by setting AutoSetRange to False and then manually specifying the LogarithmicBase for the chart axis.

</Paragraph><Paragraph TextAlignment="Center">
<Image Source="Images\Axis LogarithmicValueType Demo.png" Width="750" Height="600" /></Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Features
</Paragraph>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0">
<ListItem><Paragraph>Range and Interval of the chart axis can be auto-set or customized.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Interactive Features</Paragraph>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0">

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The Checkbox <Bold>"ISAutoSetRange"</Bold>helps to set the IsAutoSetRange property for the Chart Axis.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The text box <Bold>"LogarithmicRange"</Bold> helps to set the custom ranges. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The text box <Bold>"LogarithmicBase"</Bold> helps to set the interval of Secondary Axis.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>
 <ListItem>
<Paragraph>The text box <Bold>"DesiredIntervalsCount"</Bold> helps to set the desired intervals count of Primary Axis.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>
</List>
